        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
Everyone raves about how HP is the prime stat for us Necro's. Say why? This topic was inspired by the AA thread, where people seemed to agree that "Natural durability hands down should be your first choice, its raised my hp a ton"...

I challange anyone to give me a good reason to get HP gear over, say, FT gear, or +Mana gear, or Resist gear. What is HP good for? Only a couple things:

#1. Raiding
#2. Tanking
#3. Lifeburn
#4. Oh wait.. that's all there is.

So, unless you're a Necro who does nothing but raid, tank summoning mobs, or if Lifeburn is #1 priority for you, then [b]HP IS NOT IMPORTANT[/b]. Me, I don't raid much right now (fucking aa grind), I don't tank mobs because fear-kiting is the most efficient way to get exp, and I don't Lifeburn because I don't have the ability yet (3 points away!). So unless you can come up with other reasons why I would even need HP gear, let alone waste 12 points on ND3, you heard the truth here first.

Gear goes like this FT > Regen > HP > Mana. Throw in resists, depending on what items you get.

Necro on Vallon Zek

As far as customer service in EQ. Let's stop kidding ourselves about this, ok? It's such a pathetic argument. There is no CS in EQ. Period. - Furor

There is no cow level.
[/quote]</textarea><br>
        </td>
      </tr>

