 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Kuotat</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> It's been engrained into folks that if you say anything to anyone about key stats for a necro, it's HP.  Well yes and no.</P><P>HP = longer in Lich, which means more mana.<BR>HP = more durable for pulling<BR>HP = more durable for getting beat upon while solo or grouped<BR>HP = more survivable if your FD doesn't work<BR>HP = more survivable for nasty AE's<BR>HP = more damage delt with Lifeburn<BR>etc... we all know why having HP's is good, but...</P><P>It's all a balance.  When I look at an item I take into account a bunch of stuff.</P><P>Listed in order:<BR>Effect on the item<BR>Raw HP of the item<BR>Sta of the item, because Sta is HP<BR>Mana Regen of the item<BR>Raw Mana of the item<BR>Int of the item, because Int is Mana<BR>Resists of the item (Primarily Magic, then fire/cold and then pos/dis)</P><P>Resists vs. mana/Int flip-flops depending on what item it would replace.</P><P>When it all boils down to it HP to a necro = mana.  Necro's are most useful and efficient with their mana use when they are below 100% health.  </P><P>I wear a Gem Encrusted Ring.  I'd love to upgrade that to a HP item, but the effect it has far outweighs the benefits of a 100hp ring.  Choose to wear my rotting boots instead of boots of flowing slime, because the HP and reisists are better then the mana and +3 ticks mana regen the boots give me.  I equip my Epic instead of the Black wand of some dead dragon, because the overall usefullness of my epic is better then the the HP gain I get from the wand.  I recently ditched my Velium HP necklace for a Slime Necklace because I'm working on buidling up my resists while I keep my HP's up (I lost 10 HP, but gained +25 in different resists).  </P><P>It's all balance.  Necro's that measure their dicks by how many HP's they have regardless of anything else are just as blind as a Necro who focuses only on Int.</P><P></P><P><BR><center><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.co