        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Ravynetti</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I didn't start heavily building my HP gear before 55. Between 49 and 52 I had around 900 hp... below 55 I still had 1200 or so. I used to die. A lot. I'm talking 5-6 times a day. After reading a lot of threads on the subject on this board, I started thinking about reasons I'd get hp gear. this was before lifeburn even came out mind you, and at the time I was not in a raiding guild, and I'd never thought of ever being able to solo summoning mobs. What I came up with as reasons for HP concentartion didn't even come close to what you listed. Things which convinced me to start looking into hp gear:</P><P>1) Health Aggro. In groups, AND in my favourite solo spots at the time I was finding it very hard to keep from getting low health aggro due to lich. I'd either have to constantly tap or use ... *shudder* C2 ... 800 hp doesn't go far when you have lich up. Get down to about 40 percent life, and guess what... mobs start coming after you. Mobs that won't aggro because they're too green WILL aggro you due to low health. All the int in the world can't save you if you can't even take the 1 or 2 hits it'll take to get another root off in an enclosed space. FD? Well yeah, but I prefer not to spend most of my time waiting for mobs to wander away.</P><P>2) Charmies. For a while I was rather enamoured of the thrall of bones spell. I still am. I use it a LOT when grouping, especially if we've a backup healer and/or a general surplus of mana (Kei, whatever). An augmented, even normal charmed pet you toss a proccing weapon on can be a mean addition to an XP group. Generally I use pets that can lay out between 120 and 170 dmg a hit. If I only had 800 or 900 hp (base) I'd go down in the blink of an eye if charm broke at a bad time. An interesting note on this, an int/charisma chanter friend of mine of comparable level at the time saw how much damage my charmed pet was doing, and gave it a shot in the same group. Half an hour and 4 resses later, he decided to leave it to the person with double his HP (me).</P><P>3) Duoing/Healing. I found the later 50s (55-60) stultifyingly boring. Soloing it was beginning to wear on my mind, I was finding myself doing stupider and stupider things to try to break the boredom. So eventually I started mixing it up and duoing with a monk friend. We could easily hold bk/captain/tunnel in chard, a significant number of guards in katta, etc. Mind you, stuff I could probably solo, but w/ a partner it's a) more fun, b) faster, c) safer. Don't have to worry about any repops while medding, etc. My job was basically tap, pet, pact (and slow any undead). I could keep this up nonstop pretty much, no down time. There were times however where I would have to pact 2 or even 3 times without having the mana to tap back (Ex: on nameds, etc). I couldn't do that unless I'd had at least marginal investment in hp gear.</P><P>4) Risky transit. Not really a 'need' per se, but I find that when moving through hostile territory, with the occasional undead and see invis thing (usually when they're surrounded by 3-4 casters), a little extra health where taking a hit is unavoidabable helps.</P><P>5) What else am I gonna get serious use out of. Never out of mana anyway. Well, I take that back. I've been oom in a grinding group twice in the last month. For about 20 seconds each. Usually when the puller brings so many the chanter can't mez them all before I already find myself soloing one or two of 'em. If I'm not gonna spend the gearslots on hp gear, what am I gonna do? Spend it on int and +mana so I can *cough* twitch? OH OH !! *POINT!* <b>I noticed you play on a zek, so yeah resist gear would be a good idea for you.</b> For most bluebie players though it's an almost total waste. I can get my resists up to 120+ each and mobs 30 to 40 levels below me still land for full. Flowing thought and Regen are a no brainer to want as a primary consideration, but seriously, I can name maybe two FT items off the top of my head that I'd ever have a hope in hell of seeing that aren't already an improvement hp/sta wise.</P><P>I've played the no hp gear necro. While my current total isnt' stellar, I'd never go back to the 900 or so I'd have at 60 with just base int and mana items. Been there, done that. Died too many times with a full bar of mana, just 'cause I couldn't live long enough to feign/get a tap off.</P><P>That having been said, to each their own. You do play on a zek, so your resists must be high. I don't, so I prefer my hp high. I know necros on my same server who have 1000 hp tops and are perfectly happy. There is no 'best' equipment, merely 'best equipment for your playstyle'.</P><P></P><P> </font></td>
