        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Corto</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> HP=Mana therefore the more HPs the more mana (not true)</P><P>You want to have enough HPs that you can be efficient with your taps and use your taps before hitting about 50% HPs.  Therefore if you can tap for 750HPs then you want to have 1500HPs or more.  Of course more is better for any class for the obvious reason that you won't get killed as fast.  But the argument that HPs = mana does not make sense.</P><P>If I have 14,000 hps and someone else has 1,500 HPs for example...</P><P>We both fight the same MOB and both use the same spells.  We both end the fight at 750HPs after liching and use a tap for our last spell to bring us back to full HPs.  Now I am not levelling any faster then the other guy just because I have 14,000 hps.  Now I can certainly lich longer before tapping, but I still have to tap eventually and will have to tap the same amount of times that he does.</P><P>(I was thinking of breaking this down in some sort of table but I think it makes sense the way it is)</P><P>IMO REGEN > ALL for necros.  If I had those 14,000 HPs and the other guy had his 1,500 but he has some extra regen, then he is going to level faster then me.  He will be losing less HPs at every tick and therefore won't have to tap as often as me.  So with his regen items he is able to use our more mana efficient spells and save mana meaning that he meds to full faster and gets that next pull faster.</P><P>If I had any money to speak of, or an uberguild you better believe I would be going straight for regen items.  HP items are important, but only up to a certain point, and the statement that HPs = mana is misleading.</P><P></P><P> </font></td>
