        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> The amount of mana you can squeeze out of your hitpoints liching is equal to this.<BR>Mana = (mana gain rate/hp loss rate) * hitpoints</P><P>Mana gain rate at level 60 is:<BR>+ 35 : Arch Lich<BR>+  x : FT items and buffs, assume 0 if you're soloing<BR>= 35 mana per tick</P><P>Hp loss rate at level 60 is: (remember there still is a pvp restriction on lich spells, they only do 2/3 the damage it says in spdat)<BR>  2/3 * 53 : arch lich<BR>- 2/3 *  3 : standing regen, more for iksars of course<BR>- 2/3 *  y : which is regen from buffs AA etc etc, assume 0<BR>-        z : bard song pulse, assume 0 again<BR>= 33 hp a tick</P><P>So lets say you get a 100hp upgrade from an item, with that item you're able to squeeze out 106 more mana liching.  It's better than 1:1 ratio.  </P><P>Although, I'm beginning to see the value of resists, especially with the new changes, I can't imagine what the AE's are going to be like in PoP.  I can't really get by on just level alone even on Velious mobs, anymore.  And spending mana lifetapping because you're not resisting the AE's is a very inefficient use of it.</P><P><IMG BORDER=0 ALIGN="CENTER" WIDTH=180 HEIGHT=140 SRC="http://www3.telus.net/xarkxem/blackmage.jpg" </><BR>Valishar Sa`Veera<BR>60th Level Witchy Warlock<BR>-Acropolis-</font></td>
