        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Obtaining gear with more HP is, like others have said, increasing your survivability. I'd rather be pulling a mob everytime I hit 60%hp than when I hit 40%hp for obvious reasons.</P><P>It also means I have more a cushion if for some reason I cannot find a MoB to kill. Say I get to 60%hp, usually the time I gotta find a MoB to BoD from because I always have Lich up without exception when soloing. If I cannot find that MoB (rare but does happen on a nightly basis) I can still have Lich up safely until an appropriate MoB arrives. If my total HP determined that casting BoD wasn't completely efficient until I Lich'd down to 40%hp then I might have to find myself turning Lich off until a MoB arrived in the same situation.</P><P>Yes, HP regen > HP. But HP gives you greater defensive capacities when the shit hits the fan which as we all know is just situational.</P><P>Bonekasta, 51 Necromancer<BR>TALLON ZEK</font></td>
